ft Begs Users To Stop Using IE 6" /> <span class='overlay'></span> </a></div><div class="stories"><h2 class="entry-title"> <a href="http://mashable.com/2011/03/04/ie6-countdown/" rel="self bookmark" class='headline' title="Permanent Link to Microsoft Begs Users To Stop Using IE 6">Microsoft Begs Users To Stop Using IE 6</a> <span class="comm"><a class="comment_count" title="Comments for this story" href="http://mashable.com/2011/03/04/ie6-countdown/#comments" rel="comment"><span class="dsq-postid" rel="551073 http://mashable.com/?p=551073">View Comments</span></a></span></h2></div></li></ol> </section><div id="page_content" class="clearfix" role="main"><div id="primary" class="grid_4"> <article class="post full hreview clearfix hentry hnews" id="post-448081"> <header class="entry-title summary"><h1><a href="http://mashable.com/2010/11/20/microsoft-kinect-hacks/" class='headline source-org'>Microsoft Now &#8220;Excited&#8221; by Kinect Hacks</a></h1><div class="byline reviewer vcard meta"> <a class="author_image url" href="http://mashable.com/author/josh-catone/" rel="me"><img src="http://7.mshcdn.com/wp-content/authors/Josh%20Catone-246.jpg"  alt="Josh Catone" class="author_image photo" /></a> <time class="date dtreviewed" title="November 20, 2010 3:28 PM" datetime="Sat, 20 Nov 2010 15:28:54 -0500" pubdate="">November 20, 2010</time> by <span class="author fn n"><a href="http://mashable.com/author/josh-catone/" title="Posts by Josh Catone">Josh Catone</a></span> <span class="comm"> <a class="comment_count" title="Comments for this story" href="http://mashable.com/2010/11/20/microsoft-kinect-hacks/#comments" rel="comment"> <span class="dsq-postid" rel="448081 http://mashable.com/?p=448081">View Comments</span> </a> </span></div> </header><div class="post_share rail"><div class="large-buttons"><div class="wdt_button"><iframe id="tweet_frame_448081" name="tweet_frame_448081" class="twitter-share-button" allowtransparency="true" frameborder="0" role="presentation" scrolling="no" src="http://platform.twitter.com/widgets/tweet_button.html?url=http%3A%2F%2Fmashable.com%2F2010%2F11%2F20%2Fmicrosoft-kinect-hacks%2F&amp;via=mashabletech%20%40mashable&amp;text=Microsoft%20Now%20%22Excited%22%20by%20Kinect%20Hacks&amp;count=vertical" width="55" height="63"></iframe></div><div class="wdt_button wdt_fb"><fb:share-button href="http://mashable.com/2010/11/20/microsoft-kinect-hacks/" type="box_count"></fb:share-button></div><div class="wdt_button"><div id="su_v_448081"></div></div><div class="wdt_button"><a class="chicklet block st_email" data-uri="http://mashable.com/2010/11/20/microsoft-kinect-hacks/" data-title="Microsoft Now "Excited" by Kinect Hacks" href="javascript:">email</a></div><div class="wdt_button"><a class="chicklet block st_sharethis" data-uri="http://mashable.com/2010/11/20/microsoft-kinect-hacks/" data-title="Microsoft Now "Excited" by Kinect Hacks" href="javascript:">share</a></div></div><div class="small-buttons" style="display:none"><div class="wdt_button_min"><iframe id="tweet_frame_448081" name="tweet_frame_448081" class="twitter-share-button" allowtransparency="true" frameborder="0" role="presentation" scrolling="no" src="http://platform.twitter.com/widgets/tweet_button.html?url=http%3A%2F%2Fmashable.com%2F2010%2F11%2F20%2Fmicrosoft-kinect-hacks%2F&amp;via=mashabletech%20%40mashable&amp;text=Microsoft%20Now%20%22Excited%22%20by%20Kinect%20Hacks&amp;count=horizontal" width="110" height="20"></iframe></div><div class="wdt_button_min"><fb:share-button href="http://mashable.com/2010/11/20/microsoft-kinect-hacks/" type="button_count"></fb:share-button></div><div class="wdt_button_min"><div id="su_h_448081" style="width:75px;height:22px;"></div></div><div class="wdt_button_min"><a class="chicklet block st_email" data-uri="http://mashable.com/2010/11/20/microsoft-kinect-hacks/" data-title="Microsoft Now "Excited" by Kinect Hacks" href="javascript:">email</a></div><div class="wdt_button_min"><a class="chicklet block st_sharethis" data-uri="http://mashable.com/2010/11/20/microsoft-kinect-hacks/" data-title="Microsoft Now "Excited" by Kinect Hacks" href="javascript:">share</a></div></div></div><div class="description"><div class="post-fb-like"> <fb:like href="http://mashable.com/2010/11/20/microsoft-kinect-hacks/" width="625" height="61"></fb:like></div><div id="post-adsense"><script type="text/javascript">
		google_ad_client = "pub-9942038924324175";
		google_ad_channel = '9077376301';
		google_ad_output = 'js';
		google_max_num_ads = '3';
		google_ad_type = 'text';
		google_feedback = 'on';
	</script><script type="text/javascript" src="http://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/show_ads.js"></script></div><p><img src="http://9.mshcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/xbox-kinect.jpg" alt="" title="xbox-kinect" width="225" height="225" class="alignright size-full wp-image-448083" />Since its release November 4, &#8220;hacking&#8221; Microsoft&#8217;s <a href="http://mashable.com/tag/kinect/">Kinect</a> peripheral for the <a href="http://mashable.com/tag/xbox-360">Xbox 360</a> game consoles has become a popular Internet sport.  Now, just a couple of weeks after saying that it would &#8220;work closely with law enforcement&#8221; to keep the Kinect tamper-proof, Microsoft has apparently reversed its stance, claiming that the Kinect was left open to tinkerers on purpose.</p><p>Following a <a href="http://www.adafruit.com/blog/2010/11/04/the-open-kinect-project-the-ok-prize-get-1000-bounty-for-kinect-for-xbox-360-open-source-drivers/" target="_blank">$3,000 bounty</a> put up by the open source community for anyone able to create an open source driver for Kinect, Microsoft <a href="http://news.cnet.com/8301-13772_3-20021836-52.html" target="_blank">told <em>CNET</em></a> on November 4 that it &#8220;does not condone the modification of its products.&#8221;</p><p>A similar bounty was <a href="http://mashable.com/2010/11/12/matt-cutts-kinect-hack/">put up by Google engineer Matt Cutts</a> last week. The gamer community has found numerous alternative uses for Kinect already, including as a controller for <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ho6Yhz21BJI" target="_blank"><i>Minority Report</i>-style multitouch</a> and the ability to <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KW9of1Ud0uo" target="_blank">capture 3D video</a>.</p><p>Initially, Microsoft was not pleased with the popularity of Kinect hacking.  &#8220;With Kinect, Microsoft built in numerous hardware and software safeguards designed to reduce the chances of product tampering,&#8221; the company said in a statement to <em>CNET</em> on the day of the device&#8217;s U.S. launch. &#8220;Microsoft will continue to make advances in these types of safeguards and work closely with law enforcement and product safety groups to keep Kinect tamper-resistant.&#8221;</p><p>However, Microsoft appears to have changed its tune. On the November 19 broadcast of National Public Radio&#8217;s <a href="http://www.sciencefriday.com/program/archives/201011196" target="_blank"><i>Science Daily</i></a> program, director of incubation for Xbox Alex Kipman said that the Kinect was left open &#8220;by design.&#8221;</p><p>The full excerpt is below:</p><blockquote><p> <em>&#8220;Kinect was not actually hacked. Hacking would mean that someone got to our algorithms that sit inside of the Xbox and was able to actually use them. Which hasn&#8217;t happened. Or, it means that you put a device between the sensor and the Xbox for means of cheating, which also has not happened. That&#8217;s what we call hacking, and that&#8217;s what we put a ton of work and effort in to make sure doesn&#8217;t actually occur.</p><p>&#8220;What has happened is someone wrote a open source driver for PCs, which essentially opens the USB connection, which we didn&#8217;t protect by design, and reads the inputs from the sensor.&#8221;</em></p></blockquote><p>Kipman also said that fans &#8220;hacking&#8221; Kinect would not result in a legal action.  Fellow Microsoftie, Shannon Loftis, a studio manager at Microsoft Game Studios, said that she is &#8220;excited to see that people are so inspired&#8221; to think about what they can create using the Kinect hardware.</p><p>[<em>Via <a href="http://www.adafruit.com/blog/2010/11/19/microsoft-now-says-its-inspired-by-community-finding-new-uses-for-kinect/" target="_blank">Adafruit</a></em>]</p></div><div class="post-actions"> <a class="print_story" href="javascript:window.print();">Print Story</a> <a class="chicklet st_email" data-uri="http://mashable.com/2010/11/20/microsoft-kinect-hacks/" data-title="Microsoft Now &#8220;Excited&#8221; by Kinect Hacks" href="#">Email Story</a></div><footer class="post_footer clearfix"><h6>Topics to follow</h6><ul id="post-follow-topics" class="topics_list"><li> <a href="/follow/topics/microsoft"><img src="http://6.mshcdn.com/follow/uploads/topic/image/00/b9/5c/9b/97/41/thumb_microsoft-7894114def.jpeg" alt="Microsoft" /></a><div class="content"> <a class="topic_title" href="/follow/topics/microsoft">Microsoft</a> 12 followers</div><a class="follow_obj_link follow_link" href="/follow/topics/microsoft/follow">Follow</a></li><li> <a href="/follow/topics/xbox-360"><img src="http://api.freebase.com/api/trans/image_thumb/en/xbox_360?maxwidth=32&maxheight=32&mode=fillcrop" alt="Xbox 360" /></a><div class="content"> <a class="topic_title" href="/follow/topics/xbox-360">Xbox 360</a> 2 followers</div><a class="follow_obj_link follow_link" href="/follow/topics/xbox-360/follow">Follow</a></li><li> <a href="/follow/topics/gaming"><img src="http://6.mshcdn.com/follow/uploads/topic/image/c2/7d/6c/6b/f5/d8/thumb_gaming-b35def8993.jpeg" alt="Gaming" /></a><div class="content"> <a class="topic_title" href="/follow/topics/gaming">Gaming</a> 7 followers</div><a class="follow_obj_link follow_link" href="/follow/topics/gaming/follow">Follow</a></li><li> <a href="/follow/topics/kinect"><img src="http://api.freebase.com/api/trans/image_thumb/en/project_natal?maxwidth=32&maxheight=32&mode=fillcrop" alt="Kinect" /></a><div class="content"> <a class="topic_title" href="/follow/topics/kinect">Kinect</a> 3 followers</div><a class="follow_obj_link follow_link" href="/follow/topics/kinect/follow">Follow</a></li><li> <a href="/follow/topics/hacks"><img src="http://6.mshcdn.com/follow/images/default_topic_32x32.png" alt="Hacks" /></a><div class="content"> <a class="topic_title" href="/follow/topics/hacks">Hacks</a> 0 followers</div><a class="follow_obj_link follow_link" href="/follow/topics/hacks/follow">Follow</a></li><li> <a href="/follow/topics/matt-cutts"><img src="http://6.mshcdn.com/follow/images/default_topic_32x32.png" alt="Matt cutts" /></a><div class="content"> <a class="topic_title" href="/follow/topics/matt-cutts">Matt cutts</a> 0 followers</div><a class="follow_obj_link follow_link" href="/follow/topics/matt-cutts/follow">Follow</a></li></ul><ul id="post-follow-topics-more" class="topics_list"><li> <a href="/follow/topics/xbox-kinect"><img src="http://6.mshcdn.com/follow/images/default_topic_32x32.png" alt="Xbox Kinect" /></a><div class="content"> <a class="topic_title" href="/follow/topics/xbox-kinect">Xbox Kinect</a> 0 followers</div><a class="follow_obj_link follow_link" href="/follow/topics/xbox-kinect/follow">Follow</a></li></ul><script type="text/javascript">setupTopics();</script><hr /><h6>For more <a href="/tech/">Tech &amp; Gadgets</a> coverage</h6><ul id="for_more"><li class='twitter'> <a href="http://twitter.com/mashabletech">Follow Mashable Tech &amp; Gadgets</a></li><li class='facebook'> <a href="http://www.facebook.com/mashable.tech">Become a fan on Facebook</a></li><li class='rss'> <a href="http://feeds.mashable.com/mashable/tech">Subscribe to the Tech &amp; Gadgets channel</a></li><li class='downloads'> Download our free apps for <a href="http://mashable.com/2010/08/02/mashable-android-app/" rel="nofollow">Android</a>, <a href="http://itunes.apple.com/us/app/mashable-for-mac/id412390413?mt=12" rel="nofollow">Mac</a>, <a href="http://itunes.apple.com/us/app/mashable/id356202138?mt=8" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">iPhone</a> and <a href="http://itunes.apple.com/us/app/mashable-for-ipad/id370097986?mt=8" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">iPad</a></li></ul> </footer> </article> <section class="section list clearfix more-in"><h1 class='bar'><span>More Stories in Tech &amp; Gadgets</span></h1><ol class="rectangle_posts "><li class="post rectangle e0 t0 ct0 "><div class="image-frame"> <a class="img" href="http://mashable.com/2011/03/04/lifelike-robot/"> <img src="http://5.mshcdn.